@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Elite Athletes";
    ViewData["Page"] = "Elite Athletes";
}

<style>
    .athlete-img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 300px;
        object-fit: cover;
        object-position: center;
    }
    
    .athlete-img-top {
        object-position: top;
    }
</style>

<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Elite Athletes</h1>
        <p class="lead">If you like the olympics, track and field, inspirational people, or even if you're into anything cool then you should probably know these athletes.</p>
        <p class="text-muted">All of the following are olympic medalists.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Image Gallery -->
    <div class="row g-3 mb-5">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <img src="img/kipchoge.webp" alt="Eliud Kipchoge" class="athlete-img rounded shadow" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <img src="img/hocker.jpg" alt="Cole Hocker" class="athlete-img athlete-img-top rounded shadow" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <img src="img/jakobing.jpg" alt="Jakob Ingebrigtsen" class="athlete-img rounded shadow" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="img/kenneth.jpg" alt="Kenneth Rooks" class="athlete-img athlete-img-top rounded shadow" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="img/mondo.jpg" alt="Mondo Duplantis" class="athlete-img athlete-img-top rounded shadow" />
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Athletes Information Card -->
    <div class="card shadow">
        <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white" style="background-color: #9B5094 !important">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-0">Meet the Athletes</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body p-4">
            <div class="list-group list-group-flush">
                <div class="list-group-item">
                    <h5 class="mb-2">1. Eliud Kipchoge</h5>
                    <p class="mb-0">Kipchoge is a 2 time gold medalist in the marathon. He is also one of the most inspirational athletes of all time, one of the only known
                        to have run a marathon in under 2 hours (not officially recognized as a world record). His motto is "No human is limited".</p>
                </div>

                <div class="list-group-item">
                    <h5 class="mb-2">2. Cole Hocker</h5>
                    <p class="mb-0">Cole Hocker snuck up to win the gold in the 1500m in the 2024 Paris Olympics</p>
                </div>

                <div class="list-group-item">
                    <h5 class="mb-2">3. Jakob Ingebrigtsen</h5>
                    <p class="mb-0">Ingebrigtsen is a Norwegian two-time gold medalist. He also holds 5 ratified world records. One of the top distance runners
                        of all time. He specializes in the 1500m and 5000m, and hopes to break the outdoor world records in them in 2026.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="list-group-item">
                    <h5 class="mb-2">4. Kenneth Rooks</h5>
                    <p class="mb-0">Kenneth Rooks is a Nike athlete from Washington specializing in the 3000m Steeplechase. While attending BYU, he won the NCAA Steeplechase final even after taking a fall in the 
                        early laps of the race. In the Paris 2024 Olympics, an ambitious move with a lap to go helped him win a silver medal.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="list-group-item">
                    <h5 class="mb-2">5. Mondo Duplantis</h5>
                    <p class="mb-0">Mondo Duplantis is a pole vault athlete. He is probably one of the most dominant athletes in an event in history. He has
                        set the world record no less than 14 times, breaking his own world record every time. Also known for doing the "Turkish Guy" celebration
                        after his pole vault in the olympics.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
